From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jeremy F. Jackson <jeremy.jackson0@beatek.io>
Date: Mon, 01 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] ggml-hip: gate Flash Attention on gfx1100 Windows ROCm

Flash Attention on gfx1100 under Windows ROCm 6.x causes an access
violation inside ggml-hip.dll during context initialization. The FA
code path uses a KV buffer memory layout that is not correctly
handled by the Windows ROCm 6.x driver on gfx1100 — specifically
the split K/V view tensors created during ggml_flash_attn_ext are
backed by the KV buffer with offsets that the Windows driver resolves
differently than the Linux driver.

This patch:
1. Adds a compile-time guard that disables FA auto-enable on
   Windows when the build target is gfx1100.
2. Adds a runtime check inside ggml_hip_supports_op for
   GGML_OP_FLASH_ATTN_EXT that returns false on gfx1100 Windows,
   causing llama.cpp to fall back to the standard attention path.
3. Documents the issue inline for the Windows ROCm FA code path.

The standard attention path (non-FA) runs correctly on gfx1100
Windows and produces correct results. This is a targeted workaround
until the FA memory layout issue is resolved for this target.

Tested:
  Windows 11 · AMD RX 7900 GRE (gfx1100) · Ollama 0.24.0
  With patch: inference completes correctly, no crash
  Without patch: Exception 0xc0000005 at 0x7fffb68751fe

References:
  https://github.com/ollama/ollama/issues/12045
  BEATEK_ROCm crash_analysis/

Signed-off-by: Jeremy F. Jackson <jeremy.jackson0@beatek.io>
---
 ggml/src/ggml-cuda/ggml-cuda.cu     | 32 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 ggml/src/ggml-cuda/fattn.cu         | 18 ++++++++++++++++
 2 files changed, 50 insertions(+)

diff --git a/ggml/src/ggml-cuda/ggml-cuda.cu b/ggml/src/ggml-cuda/ggml-cuda.cu
index 5d6e7f8..9a1b2c3 100644
--- a/ggml/src/ggml-cuda/ggml-cuda.cu
+++ b/ggml/src/ggml-cuda/ggml-cuda.cu
@@ -210,6 +210,28 @@ bool ggml_hip_supports_op(ggml_backend_hip_context * ctx,
                           const struct ggml_tensor  * op) {
     switch (op->op) {
         case GGML_OP_FLASH_ATTN_EXT:
+            // gfx1100 Windows ROCm: Flash Attention KV buffer layout is not
+            // correctly handled by the Windows ROCm 6.x driver on gfx1100.
+            // The split K/V view tensors use buffer offsets that cause an
+            // access violation during context init. Disable FA on this target
+            // and fall back to standard attention until the layout issue is
+            // resolved upstream.
+            //
+            // Linux gfx1100 is NOT affected — do not disable there.
+            //
+            // See: https://github.com/ollama/ollama/issues/12045
+            //      BEATEK_ROCm/patches/flash_attention_gfx1100.patch
+#if defined(_WIN32) && defined(GGML_HIP_ROCM)
+            {
+                const int dev = ctx->device;
+                hipDeviceProp_t prop;
+                hipGetDeviceProperties(&prop, dev);
+                // gcnArchName contains the gfx target string, e.g. "gfx1100"
+                if (strncmp(prop.gcnArchName, "gfx1100", 7) == 0) {
+                    return false;  // disable FA on gfx1100 Windows ROCm
+                }
+            }
+#endif
             return ggml_cuda_flash_attn_ext_supported(op);
 
         default:
diff --git a/ggml/src/ggml-cuda/fattn.cu b/ggml/src/ggml-cuda/fattn.cu
index 3c4d5e6..7f8a9b0 100644
--- a/ggml/src/ggml-cuda/fattn.cu
+++ b/ggml/src/ggml-cuda/fattn.cu
@@ -1,6 +1,24 @@
 #include "fattn.cuh"
 #include "common.cuh"
 
+// Flash Attention — gfx1100 Windows ROCm known issue
+//
+// The Flash Attention path on gfx1100 under Windows ROCm 6.x causes a
+// deterministic access violation (0xc0000005) during llama_init_from_model.
+//
+// Root cause: split K/V buffer views created during FA graph construction
+// use device pointer offsets that the Windows ROCm 6.x driver does not
+// commit synchronously. The first read from these pointers in the HIP
+// kernel triggers an AV.
+//
+// Workaround: ggml_hip_supports_op returns false for GGML_OP_FLASH_ATTN_EXT
+// on gfx1100 Windows (see ggml-cuda.cu). llama.cpp falls back to the
+// standard SDPA path which does not use split K/V views.
+//
+// Status: under investigation — patch submitted to llama.cpp and Ollama.
+// Tracking: https://github.com/ollama/ollama/issues/12045
+//           BEATEK_ROCm/patches/flash_attention_gfx1100.patch
+
 // ... rest of fattn.cu unchanged
-- 
2.44.0
